[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The Commission’s work programme will run until 
[normal]Octo
[normal]ber
[normal] 2014 through three main strands: 
[normal]a call for 
[normal]evidence; commissioned research; and high level seminars and roundtables
[normal]. A
[normal] final 
[normal]report 
[normal]will be 
[normal]published at the end of the process, includ
[normal]ing
[normal] detailed recommendations.
[normal] 
[normal]W
[normal]ork will focus particular
[normal]ly
[normal] on
[normal]:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Skills and labour markets,[bold] and how to align decision making and funding of skills agendas at local and national level.
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Infrastructure, connectivity, and clustering,[bold] includ
[normal]ing 
[normal]housing, transport, 
[normal]and 
[normal]digital
[normal]. 
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Fiscal and policy devolution[bold], 
[normal]includ
[normal]ing
[normal] cities’ freedom to borrow to invest 
[normal]and to maximise their 
[normal]competitiveness.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The Secretariat will be hosted by the RSA, which has run several important and influential Commissions
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]For example, the 
[normal]2020 Public Services Commission
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]c
[normal]haired by Sir Andrew Fos
[normal]ter
[normal], was influential in shaping the public service reform agenda prior
[normal] to 
[normal]and following – the 2010 election by bringing together 
[normal]a range of 
[normal]perspectives 
[normal]across the political spectrum, academia, 
[normal]and 
[normal]public, private and voluntary sectors.   
[normal]Other examples in
[normal]clude the 
[normal]Academies Commission (
[normal]c
[normal]haired by Christine Gilbert), and
[normal], currently, 
[normal]the Independent Review of the Police Federation
[normal] (
[normal]chaired by Sir David Normington
[normal])
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]During the course of the Commission’s Inquiry we will publish reports and papers on our findi
[normal]ngs as they emerge.  The first of these will be a scene setter looking at the factors which are driving growth in cities globally, and the challenges and opportunities that thes
[normal]e throw up for British cities. 
[normal]In the Spring
[normal] we will also host some evidence sessions across the country
[normal], after which w
[normal]e anticipate being in a position to discuss some of our emerging findings. If that dovetails with your timescales for oral evidence then I or one of my Commissioner 
[normal]c
[normal]olleagues would
[normal] be pleased to provide evidence 
[normal]at a future hearing of the 
[normal]Communities and Local Government Committee’s inquiry.  
[normal]I look forward to hearing from you in due course.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Jim O’Neill
